summary:
Fixed silent truncation bug.

Root cause:
process_file() used a fixed 64 KB stack buffer and file.read(&mut buffer), so inputs larger than 64 KB were silently truncated.

Fix:
Changed process_file() to read the entire file into a Vec<u8> with read_to_end, eliminating the size limit.

src/main.rs diff (essentials):

- let mut buffer = [0u8; BUFFER_SIZE];
- let bytes_read = file.read(&mut buffer)?;
- let data = &buffer[..bytes_read];
- let transformed = transform::process(data);

+ let mut buffer = Vec::new();
+ file.read_to_end(&mut buffer)?;
+ let transformed = transform::process(&buffer);

Run the provided test:

./test.sh  
PASS: File processed correctly, no data loss

The binary now preserves files of any size (limited only by available memory).
